Interface TypeWriter.InMethodPhase<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The best known loaded type for the dynamically created type.

    TypeWriter<T>

    TypeWriter<T>

    public static interface TypeWriter.InMethodPhase<T>
extends TypeWriter<T>
    Describes a type writer currently in the method phase, i.e. in the phase after any type meta information is added to a type and after its fields are written.

        TypeWriter.InMethodPhase<T> write(java.lang.Iterable<? extends MethodDescription> methodDescriptions,
                                  TypeWriter.MethodPool methodPool)
        Adds a number of methods as described by the argument to the type that is created by this type writer where the implementations and annotations are received from the given compiled method registry.
        Parameters:
        methodDescriptions - The methods to be added to the type that is created by this type writer.
        methodPool - The method pool that is queried for creating implementations for these methods.
        Returns:
        This type writer.
